description: For sale: $289,900. You don't want to miss out on this one-of-a-kind incredible custom-built home. Enjoy the beauty of hardwood floor upper l2015. Roof 2015, new kitchen flooring, stove 2019, lower level carpet installed by Home Depot in 2015, fully fenced with chain link, boiler tuned up Feb 2020, concrete driveway, updated washer & dryer. Half of the large family room in the lower level could be converted into a bedroom. Enjoy family time around the beautiful spacious deck. There are 2 bedrooms on the upper level with a full bath & ¾ bath in the master BR. Transition to the basement with a big open family room & the 3rd bedroom. The lower level family room with its fireplace would be fantastic for movie nights or overflow guest space. Many interior areas were painted recently. Just six miles distance to Downtown MPLS. Few parks including the Silverwood Park (popular with an island) is a mile or two away distance. This is a great location and opportunity. Move-in and enjoy!

For sale: $300,000. Silver Lake Village offers luxury living and convenient amenities wrapped in a beautiful modern community. This unique southeast facing corner condo has two access points including one directly through a private porch! Tremendous space with 2 bedrooms and an office. The open floor plan features an abundance of natural light, a gas burning fireplace and modern kitchen. This summer take time relaxing on your private porch with views of the pond. Enjoy the gas fireplace and in-unit laundry. The community boasts two large exercise rooms with equipment, party room with full kitchen, and guest suites for those visiting. The large courtyard offers patio, gas grills, tables and fire pit. Just steps from the condo is Salo Park and the amphitheater with outdoor summer concerts! You will be located within an easy commute to both downtowns as well as the U of MN. Walk to one of the many eateries or for a quick trip to the market.

For sale: $115,000. Condo living at it's finest. Open kitchen to the dining area and living room. A 3+ season deck that has screens, shades and windows is connected to the living room. The bathroom tub has a step in making showering safe. The building has many amenities. They include a underground parking spot, car wash, library, on floor laundry and a meeting place for social activities. Very clean building that is close to Central Avenue and the bus line. A great place to call home.

For sale: $325,000. Quality rehabbed 3 bedroom 2 bathroom rambler with finished lower level.  Home features: new kitchen with snack bar, white cabinets, stainless steel appliances,  hardwood floors, tile backsplash; white trim and neutral color throughout; new carpet; new windows; new mechanicals; new maintenance-free siding.Brand new 2-car garage.  Large backyard to spend time in.  Close to parks, trails, schools and shopping.  Easy highway and mass transit access.  A must see!

For sale: $449,900. Meticulously cared for and maintained home in Columbia Heights! This beautiful 4 bedroom, 4 bathroom home has all of the design selections you desire in your new home! description:
Recently sold: $230,000. Zillow estimate now at 286$ with $35k for 50 solar panels and rebates. $5k RV/ elec car outlet and 3rd driveway, 200 amp box. Low maintenance, pollinator wood chips, no lawn. Garden. 
Cheery Heights complex: all at $280k and above. Single owner. 

Greenhabbed and remodeled.

Space heaters downstairs covered by solar. Well maintained furnace. 

http://gis.anokacountymn.gov/webgis/?pin=25-30-24-32-0013

Roof 2006/2016, Vinyl siding, new concrete driveway. 
Hardwood floors light bamboo upstairs to match honey oak cabinets, dark cherry 1 bedroom upstairs. Heated tile downstairs. Disabilty modifications grab bars. 

Replaced insulation to 17 in, most windows, door, deck, garage door opener.  

Now with some carpet in basement, new black kitchen appliances with french door fridge, new lights and toilets and more. 

Locked mailbox, storage shelves in garage, epoxy garage floor and porch, and shed. Painted deck and new railing.

 1/4 acre next to high school football field. Neighbors have no fences so wide open spaces. Garden, bee and bat habitats under deck. 

No mow lawn with red mulch and front lawn perennials flower garden and path.  200 bulbs planted. 

Garage epoxy coat: partial. 3 large metal musclerack shelves, 2 huge built in wood ones. Large storage shed in back with shelves. 

Blvd: with Glads and plantings

Back stone: planted with hostas coming in, a row of lilles and a top of Rembrandt tulips. 

Also ferns, bandcamp, bee balm

Garden with tomatoes and many onions planted. Squash and pumpkins started. 

Rv outlet. Possible parking with more paving. 

1 yr AHS home warranty

Recently sold: $270,000. Ryland Home's largest floor plan, The Jamesburg. Home nestled at end of street and near Huset Park and city hall. Great location near downtown. Featuring 9 feet main floor, maple trim and cabinets, kitchen granite countertops, stainless steal appliances, enlarged island, huge master bedroom with sitting area and vaulted ceiling, walk in closet, master bath with shower/soak tub, recessed lights and satin nickel hardware throughout, lower level can be set up as 4th bedroom or recreation room. Move in ready!

Three good sized bedrooms on the main level with French doors leading to a fully screened in porch! Perfect place to enjoy your morning coffee. Recently sold: $50,000. This is a Gobble of a Good Deal! 

If you submit an application and are approved before November 21, 2018 you will receive ONE MONTH FREE RENT and $50 gift card towards your holiday meal. Terms and conditions apply to both offers.

Looking for a nice quiet place to call home for a long time?  THIS IS THE ONE!
Are your favorite roommates the ones with 4 paws?  THIS IS THE HOUSE FOR YOU!
(please see pet restrictions below)

Sweet little house- location is on the corner sharing a beautiful open lot, no neighbors.
Serenity in the city.

Move into all new carpet in bedrooms, all new window and light fixtures, fresh paint all around. Just updated.

Front and back entrances, 1 off street driveway parking space (there is more off street parking available if needed)

Main Floor:

Kitchen - nice and basic with dining area, tons of cabinets, gas stove

3 bedrooms- 2 are smaller- fits a double or twin bed and a couple of dressers, the 3rd bedroom is bigger easily fitting a queen bed.
Basic but good size living room with hardwood floors

Lower Level:
Bathroom is downstairs (nice for privacy and sleeping if you have roommates). Basic bathroom with standing shower (no tub). There is an additional sink/counter separate from the bathroom and additional space great for storage.
 Located 1 block from Central Ave on 41st, right on the NE Minneapolis/Columbia Heights Border- everything you want and need is right around the corner- transportation, public library, restaurants. Connecting highways, Menards, Home Depot, Target within a mile.

Really-just the house on a huge empty lot, across the street is a church, the other side the fire department, and a meditation center across the alley. If you like serenity in the city- this is your house.

No more than 3 people.
Pets are negotiable- prefer no more than 2 cats or 1 dog under 30 pounds or 2 dogs under 12 pounds. Number of pets allowed is dependent on how many people/human occupancy. Pet deposits and fees apply.

$45 application fee per adult. Sorry, this home does not accept subsidy programs/Section 8. 
Monthly income must be 2.5x the rent amount, no evictions/UD's, no felonies.

Recently sold: $195,000. Charming home in Columbia Heights. 3 bedroom 1 bath. Gleaming hardwood flooring throughout. Formal dining room. Spacious lower level family room. Large 20 x 13 upper-level master bedroom. Lots of natural light.
